WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:02.436 --> 00:00:03.285
NARRATOR:
<i>Previously on</i> Teen Wolf...

2
00:00:03.353 --> 00:00:03.852
What's wrong? Get away.

3
00:00:03.921 --> 00:00:05.437
Scott?

4
00:00:05.506 --> 00:00:07.606
Derek! I need your help.

5
00:00:07.675 --> 00:00:10.191
You want to know
if you'll hurt her.

6
00:00:10.260 --> 00:00:12.144
But it's not gonna
come for free.

7
00:00:12.213 --> 00:00:14.474
Don't think for a second I've given up
on finding out what your little secret is.

8
00:00:14.498 --> 00:00:16.008
I think whatever
it is you are hiding.

9
00:00:16.032 --> 00:00:17.944
you don't want her to
find out about it. either.

10
00:00:17.968 --> 00:00:19.118
Think about me.

11
00:00:19.186 --> 00:00:20.186
Naked.

12
00:00:22.823 --> 00:00:24.067
I'm not big on group dates.

13
00:00:24.091 --> 00:00:26.274
Next time. just the two of us.

14
00:00:26.343 --> 00:00:27.583
You ruined my life!

15
00:00:27.611 --> 00:00:28.838
I'm not the one that bit you.

16
00:00:28.862 --> 00:00:30.411
(SCREAMING)

17
00:00:30.480 --> 00:00:32.280
There's another.
It's called an Alpha.

18
00:00:32.333 --> 00:00:34.967
He's the one that bit you.
You're part of his pack.

19
00:00:42.809 --> 00:00:45.472
NEWSCASTER ON RADIO: <i>In other
news. local authorities remain perplexed</i>

20
00:00:45.496 --> 00:00:47.240
<i>by the animal attacks
plaguing Beacon Hills.</i>

21
00:00:47.264 --> 00:00:48.780
(SCOFFS)

22
00:00:48.848 --> 00:00:50.081
<i>(MY DARLING</i> PLAYING)

23
00:00:50.150 --> 00:00:52.651
<i>♪ Don't you wanna fall asleep</i>

24
00:00:52.720 --> 00:00:56.454
<i>♪ Forget about tomorrow</i>

25
00:00:56.523 --> 00:00:59.424
<i>♪ Close your
eyes. but not to weep</i>

26
00:00:59.493 --> 00:01:00.709
(GROWLS)

27
00:01:00.777 --> 00:01:03.194
<i>♪ Forget about your sorrow ♪</i>

28
00:01:07.434 --> 00:01:09.167
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

29
00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:17.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

30
00:01:45.655 --> 00:01:46.671
(GASPS)

31
00:01:46.724 --> 00:01:47.724
(TIRES SCREECHING)

32
00:01:47.791 --> 00:01:49.257
(HORN HONKING)

33
00:01:49.326 --> 00:01:50.392
(SIGHS)

34
00:01:51.995 --> 00:01:54.846
Nice driving. Kate. Nice.

35
00:01:58.752 --> 00:01:59.792
(SIGHS)

36
00:02:02.189 --> 00:02:03.621
(LOUD CLANK)

37
00:02:03.690 --> 00:02:05.424
(THUDDING)

38
00:02:10.046 --> 00:02:11.129
(SCREAMS)

39
00:02:11.198 --> 00:02:12.497
(GRUNTING)

40
00:02:13.400 --> 00:02:15.400
No.

41
00:02:19.456 --> 00:02:20.923
(COCKS RIFLE)

42
00:02:23.160 --> 00:02:26.895
Come on. Come on!

43
00:02:37.107 --> 00:02:38.373
(GUNSHOT)

44
00:02:46.433 --> 00:02:48.099
(HOWLING)

45
00:03:12.609 --> 00:03:15.009
ALLISON: What's going on?

46
00:03:15.078 --> 00:03:17.729
Your Aunt Kate just texted.
I'm heading out to pick her up.

47
00:03:17.797 --> 00:03:19.642
It's 2:00 in the morning.
Is everything okay?

48
00:03:19.666 --> 00:03:21.160
Yeah. yeah. She's just
having a little car trouble.

49
00:03:21.184 --> 00:03:22.450
Not serious. is it?

50
00:03:22.519 --> 00:03:25.687
No. just a flat tire. Go
back to bed. sweetheart.

51
00:03:42.756 --> 00:03:44.489
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

52
00:03:45.826 --> 00:03:47.058
(GROWLS)

53
00:04:22.045 --> 00:04:23.378
(GROANING)

54
00:04:25.716 --> 00:04:27.215
(VEHICLE REVS)

55
00:04:35.726 --> 00:04:36.726
(COUGHS)

56
00:04:36.794 --> 00:04:38.359
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

57
00:04:38.962 --> 00:04:40.228
Oh...

58
00:04:40.297 --> 00:04:41.697
(GROANING)

59
00:04:45.002 --> 00:04:47.780
Get in. Not even.
"Hello. nice to see you"?

60
00:04:47.804 --> 00:04:49.304
All I've got at the moment is

61
00:04:49.373 --> 00:04:51.651
"Please put the assault rifle
away before someone notices."

62
00:04:51.675 --> 00:04:54.976
(SCOFFS) That's the brother I
love. Chris. there were two of them.

63
00:04:55.045 --> 00:04:56.344
CHRIS: The Alpha?

64
00:04:56.413 --> 00:04:59.141
KATE: I don't know. But
one of them tried to kill me.

65
00:04:59.165 --> 00:05:00.876
CHRIS: One of them is
gonna lead us to the other.

66
00:05:00.900 --> 00:05:02.867
He can't do that if he's dead.

67
00:05:02.936 --> 00:05:06.216
I can't help kill either of them
if one of them kills me first.

68
00:05:09.409 --> 00:05:11.209
How long will it take?

69
00:05:11.277 --> 00:05:13.144
I'd give him 48 hours.

70
00:05:14.931 --> 00:05:16.164
If that.

71
00:05:16.233 --> 00:05:17.832
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

72
00:05:21.455 --> 00:05:22.754
(GROANING)

73
00:05:22.823 --> 00:05:24.556
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

74
00:05:44.494 --> 00:05:45.794
Whoo!

75
00:05:45.879 --> 00:05:47.412
(BOTH LAUGHING)

76
00:05:49.399 --> 00:05:53.635
I don't see you for a year. and you
turn into a freaking runway model?

77
00:05:53.703 --> 00:05:56.904
Look at you. Oh! I hate you.

78
00:05:56.973 --> 00:05:58.557
I haven't even showered yet.

79
00:05:58.625 --> 00:06:00.592
Sweetie. you're a
knockout. In fact.

80
00:06:00.661 --> 00:06:03.606
I hope you have the boys knocking
each other's teeth out for your attention.

81
00:06:03.630 --> 00:06:04.812
I kind of have one.

82
00:06:04.898 --> 00:06:06.138
You kind of have one?

83
00:06:06.165 --> 00:06:08.161
You should kind
of have a million.

84
00:06:08.185 --> 00:06:09.751
(BOTH LAUGHING)

85
00:06:09.820 --> 00:06:12.380
Do you need some help
unpacking? No. not that one.

86
00:06:13.924 --> 00:06:16.024
Oh.

87
00:06:16.093 --> 00:06:21.312
See. you turn out beautiful. and I
end up with this kung fu death grip.

88
00:06:21.381 --> 00:06:23.292
Sorry. sweetie. I didn't
mean to be so rough.

89
00:06:23.316 --> 00:06:24.616
No worries.

90
00:06:26.286 --> 00:06:27.913
Hey. is everything
okay with your car?

91
00:06:27.937 --> 00:06:29.471
Uh. yeah.

92
00:06:29.539 --> 00:06:32.524
I just needed a
jump-start. That's all.

93
00:06:32.593 --> 00:06:34.593
A jump-start?

94
00:06:50.077 --> 00:06:54.246
If Derek isn't the Alpha. if he's not
the one who bit you. then who did?

95
00:06:56.283 --> 00:06:58.149
I don't know.

96
00:06:58.202 --> 00:07:00.435
Did the Alpha
kill the bus driver?

97
00:07:01.871 --> 00:07:03.138
I don't know.

98
00:07:05.676 --> 00:07:07.742
(SIGHS)

99
00:07:07.811 --> 00:07:10.891
Does Allison's dad know
about the... I don't know!

100
00:07:14.201 --> 00:07:15.300
Jeez.

101
00:07:15.952 --> 00:07:17.151
(SIGHS)

102
00:07:22.176 --> 00:07:25.393
Dude. you need to study more.

103
00:07:25.462 --> 00:07:29.664
That was a joke. Scott. it's one
test. You're gonna make it up.

104
00:07:29.733 --> 00:07:31.032
Do you want help studying?

105
00:07:31.101 --> 00:07:32.400
(SIGHS) No.

106
00:07:32.469 --> 00:07:35.203
I'm studying with
Allison after school today.

107
00:07:35.272 --> 00:07:37.355
That's my boy.
We're just studying.

108
00:07:37.424 --> 00:07:39.574
Uh-uh. No. you're not. I'm not?

109
00:07:39.643 --> 00:07:42.444
Not if I'm forced to live
vicariously through you.

110
00:07:42.512 --> 00:07:45.513
If you go to her house today and
squander that colossal opportunity.

111
00:07:45.582 --> 00:07:49.317
I swear to God I'll have
you de-balled. Okay.

112
00:07:49.386 --> 00:07:52.454
Just stop with the
questions. man.

113
00:07:53.357 --> 00:07:56.023
Done. No more questions.

114
00:07:56.092 --> 00:07:59.628
No more talk about
the Alpha or Derek.

115
00:07:59.696 --> 00:08:03.632
Especially Derek.
who still scares me.

116
00:08:26.740 --> 00:08:28.806
Where's Scott McCall?

117
00:08:30.810 --> 00:08:32.059
Why should I tell you?

118
00:08:32.128 --> 00:08:33.795
Because I asked you politely.

119
00:08:33.863 --> 00:08:35.596
And I only do that once.

120
00:08:35.665 --> 00:08:37.966
Hmm. Okay. tough guy.

121
00:08:38.034 --> 00:08:42.537
How about I help you find him if
you tell me what you're selling him?

122
00:08:42.606 --> 00:08:45.873
What is it? Is it Dianabol?

123
00:08:46.810 --> 00:08:48.559
Hmm?

124
00:08:48.628 --> 00:08:51.763
HGH? Steroids?

125
00:08:52.732 --> 00:08:54.783
No. Girl Scout Cookies.

126
00:08:54.851 --> 00:08:58.320
What the hell do you
think I'm talking about?

127
00:08:58.388 --> 00:09:00.888
By the way. whatever
it is you're selling.

128
00:09:00.957 --> 00:09:03.124
I'd probably stop
sampling the merchandise.

129
00:09:03.193 --> 00:09:05.443
You look wrecked.

130
00:09:13.954 --> 00:09:15.420
I'll find him myself.

131
00:09:15.488 --> 00:09:17.321
No. we're not done here.

132
00:09:19.359 --> 00:09:21.092
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

133
00:09:36.376 --> 00:09:38.576
(CHALK WRITING ON CHALKBOARD)

134
00:09:44.584 --> 00:09:46.284
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

135
00:09:46.353 --> 00:09:49.114
MAN: <i>I finish lacrosse practice
at 5:00. I'll be over after that.</i>

136
00:09:49.806 --> 00:09:51.956
(CLICKING)

137
00:09:52.009 --> 00:09:53.169
<i>Scott's coming over. tonight?</i>

138
00:09:53.193 --> 00:09:54.737
<i>We're just studying together.</i>

139
00:09:54.761 --> 00:09:56.873
LYDIA: <i>Just studying
never ends with just studying.</i>

140
00:09:56.897 --> 00:09:59.497
It's like getting
into a hot tub.

141
00:09:59.565 --> 00:10:01.310
Somebody eventually cops a feel.

142
00:10:01.334 --> 00:10:03.601
So. what are you saying?

143
00:10:03.670 --> 00:10:07.238
I'm just saying. you know.
make sure he covers up.

144
00:10:07.841 --> 00:10:09.140
(CHUCKLES)

145
00:10:09.209 --> 00:10:12.576
Hello. Snow White. I'm
talking about a condom.

146
00:10:12.645 --> 00:10:15.546
(CHUCKLES) Are you
kidding? After one date?

147
00:10:15.615 --> 00:10:17.994
Don't be a total prude.
Give him a little taste.

148
00:10:18.018 --> 00:10:21.485
Well. I mean. how
much is a little taste?

149
00:10:21.554 --> 00:10:24.267
LYDIA: <i>Oh. God. You
really like him. don't you?</i>

150
00:10:24.291 --> 00:10:26.757
ALLISON: <i>Well.
he's just different.</i>

151
00:10:26.827 --> 00:10:29.944
<i>When I first moved here I had
a plan. no boyfriends till college.</i>

152
00:10:30.012 --> 00:10:35.366
I just move too much. But then
I met him. and he was different.

153
00:10:37.037 --> 00:10:39.504
I don't know. I
can't explain it.

154
00:10:39.572 --> 00:10:43.474
I can. It's your brain flooding
with phenylethylamine.

155
00:10:43.543 --> 00:10:45.543
(LAUGHS) What?

156
00:10:47.514 --> 00:10:50.315
I'll tell you what to do.
When's he coming over?

157
00:10:50.384 --> 00:10:52.444
Right after school. Hmm.

158
00:10:52.468 --> 00:10:53.601
(BELL RINGING)

159
00:11:01.394 --> 00:11:02.794
(ROCK MUSIC)

160
00:11:18.928 --> 00:11:19.977
(TIRES SCREECH)

161
00:11:20.046 --> 00:11:22.146
Oh. my God.

162
00:11:22.215 --> 00:11:23.697
(HORN HONKING)

163
00:11:27.453 --> 00:11:29.454
No. no. no. no. Not here.

164
00:11:31.524 --> 00:11:33.519
You gotta be kidding me.
This guy's everywhere.

165
00:11:33.543 --> 00:11:35.075
(HORNS HONKING)

166
00:11:37.397 --> 00:11:41.599
What the hell? What
are you doing here?

167
00:11:42.969 --> 00:11:44.169
I was shot.

168
00:11:44.237 --> 00:11:46.298
He's not looking so good. dude.

169
00:11:46.322 --> 00:11:47.655
Why aren't you healing?

170
00:11:47.724 --> 00:11:49.357
I can't.

171
00:11:49.425 --> 00:11:51.954
It was a different kind
of bullet. A silver bullet?

172
00:11:51.978 --> 00:11:53.294
No. you idiot.

173
00:11:53.363 --> 00:11:56.798
Wait. That' what she meant
when she said you had 48 hours.

174
00:11:56.866 --> 00:12:00.168
What? Who said 48 hours?

175
00:12:00.236 --> 00:12:01.603
The one who shot you.

176
00:12:02.722 --> 00:12:04.372
(GROANING)

177
00:12:04.440 --> 00:12:06.140
(HORNS HONKING)

178
00:12:06.209 --> 00:12:08.776
What are you doing? Stop that.

179
00:12:08.845 --> 00:12:10.695
That's what I'm trying
to tell you. I can't.

180
00:12:11.214 --> 00:12:13.198
Derek. get up.

181
00:12:19.472 --> 00:12:21.005
(HORNS HONKING)

182
00:12:33.036 --> 00:12:35.420
Help me put him in your car.

183
00:12:36.956 --> 00:12:38.439
(HORNS HONKING)

184
00:12:38.508 --> 00:12:40.519
I need you to find out what
kind of bullet they used.

185
00:12:40.543 --> 00:12:41.871
How the hell am I
supposed to do that?

186
00:12:41.895 --> 00:12:43.606
She's an Argent.
She's with them.

187
00:12:43.630 --> 00:12:45.279
Why should I help you?

188
00:12:45.348 --> 00:12:46.588
Because you need me.

189
00:12:49.502 --> 00:12:52.637
Fine. I'll try.

190
00:12:52.705 --> 00:12:54.405
(SIGHS) Hey. get
him out of here.

191
00:12:54.473 --> 00:12:56.857
I hate you for this so much.

192
00:12:56.926 --> 00:12:59.427
Hey. what was he doing here?

193
00:12:59.495 --> 00:13:01.996
Stiles was just
giving him a ride.

194
00:13:02.064 --> 00:13:03.414
Uh. long story.

195
00:13:03.483 --> 00:13:05.077
I thought you said you
weren't friends with him.

196
00:13:05.101 --> 00:13:08.436
No. Not really. Um. we're
still studying together. right?

197
00:13:08.504 --> 00:13:11.183
So I'll meet you back
at your place? Yeah.

198
00:13:11.207 --> 00:13:13.524
Okay. bye. See you there.

199
00:13:21.484 --> 00:13:23.084
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

200
00:13:29.425 --> 00:13:31.075
(ENERGETIC MUSIC)

201
00:13:35.131 --> 00:13:36.397
(BICYCLE TIRES SCREECH)

202
00:13:41.420 --> 00:13:45.038
How did you... You got
here the same time I did.

203
00:13:47.277 --> 00:13:52.463
Oh. yeah. I just took a
shortcut. A really short shortcut.

204
00:13:52.532 --> 00:13:55.382
What is going on with you today?
You are acting all kinds of bizarre.

205
00:13:55.451 --> 00:13:56.512
(SIGHS)

206
00:13:56.536 --> 00:14:01.239
I'm just stressing
about classes.

207
00:14:01.307 --> 00:14:03.891
I'm not doing as good this year.

208
00:14:03.960 --> 00:14:05.776
Not doing as well.

209
00:14:05.828 --> 00:14:08.262
See? Exactly.

210
00:14:08.331 --> 00:14:10.331
Maybe we should
start with English?

211
00:14:10.400 --> 00:14:11.633
(LAUGHS)

212
00:14:14.737 --> 00:14:16.287
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

213
00:14:20.226 --> 00:14:23.294
Don't worry. Nobody's gonna
be home for hours. Come on.

214
00:14:24.046 --> 00:14:25.697
Okay.

215
00:14:26.499 --> 00:14:27.998
(UPBEAT MUSIC)

216
00:14:43.366 --> 00:14:46.234
I'm still unpacking.

217
00:14:46.302 --> 00:14:49.937
Uh. haven't you been
here for. like. over a month?

218
00:14:50.940 --> 00:14:52.940
I'm taking my time.

219
00:14:55.512 --> 00:14:56.677
Hey. um...

220
00:14:56.746 --> 00:15:02.550
So I figured that
we'd start with history.

221
00:15:08.174 --> 00:15:10.158
(UPBEAT ELECTRONIC MUSIC)

222
00:15:40.173 --> 00:15:41.572
What's wrong?

223
00:15:41.640 --> 00:15:45.509
Um... Nothing. I just...

224
00:15:45.578 --> 00:15:47.522
I don't wanna make you feel
like you have to do something

225
00:15:47.546 --> 00:15:48.896
you don't wanna do.

226
00:15:48.965 --> 00:15:52.005
I'm not doing anything I
don't want to do. Are you?

227
00:15:53.819 --> 00:15:56.553
You're seriously
asking me that question?

228
00:15:57.523 --> 00:15:59.273
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

229
00:16:02.645 --> 00:16:05.145
Are you going to answer that?

230
00:16:05.214 --> 00:16:08.248
Yeah. it's probably just Stiles.

231
00:16:08.317 --> 00:16:11.052
It'll go to voicemail.
Eventually.

232
00:16:12.372 --> 00:16:13.621
(RINGING CONTINUES)

233
00:16:13.689 --> 00:16:15.022
Wait!

234
00:16:16.158 --> 00:16:17.258
Um...

235
00:16:18.694 --> 00:16:21.796
Uh. yeah. I should
answer it now.

236
00:16:27.102 --> 00:16:29.303
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO)

237
00:16:34.410 --> 00:16:38.996
Come on. Try not to bleed
out on my seats. okay?

238
00:16:39.065 --> 00:16:40.759
We're almost there.
Almost where?

239
00:16:40.783 --> 00:16:42.600
(SIGHS) Your house.

240
00:16:42.668 --> 00:16:44.619
What? No. you
can't take me there.

241
00:16:44.687 --> 00:16:46.114
I can't take you to
your own house?

242
00:16:46.138 --> 00:16:48.018
Not when I can't protect myself.

243
00:16:54.397 --> 00:16:57.637
What happens if Scott doesn't
find your little magic bullet? Hmm?

244
00:16:57.717 --> 00:17:01.769
Are you dying? Not
yet. I have a last resort.

245
00:17:01.838 --> 00:17:04.455
What do you mean?
What last resort?

246
00:17:04.507 --> 00:17:07.341
Oh. my God! What is that?

247
00:17:07.409 --> 00:17:11.011
Oh. is that contagious? You know
what. you should probably just get out.

248
00:17:11.080 --> 00:17:13.464
Start the car. Now.

249
00:17:13.532 --> 00:17:16.361
I don't think you should be
barking orders with the way you look.

250
00:17:16.385 --> 00:17:18.569
In fact. I think if I wanted to.

251
00:17:18.638 --> 00:17:20.383
I could probably drag
your little werewolf ass

252
00:17:20.407 --> 00:17:22.751
out into the middle of the
road and leave you for dead.

253
00:17:22.775 --> 00:17:27.445
Start the car. or I'm gonna rip
your throat out with my teeth.

254
00:17:32.101 --> 00:17:33.634
(ENGINE STARTS)

255
00:17:35.121 --> 00:17:37.855
(INDIE ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

256
00:17:37.924 --> 00:17:40.057
It's off. Sorry about that.

257
00:17:48.935 --> 00:17:50.384
Who's this?

258
00:17:50.453 --> 00:17:52.364
That's my dad's sister. Kate.

259
00:17:52.388 --> 00:17:55.301
Except she's more like my
sister. She got here last night.

260
00:17:55.325 --> 00:17:56.724
Uh. last night?

261
00:17:56.793 --> 00:17:59.226
Yep. she had some car trouble.

262
00:18:00.146 --> 00:18:01.645
I guess.

263
00:18:02.465 --> 00:18:04.565
She looks familiar.

264
00:18:04.634 --> 00:18:08.234
Mmm. She actually used to live in
Beacon Hills. Maybe you saw her once.

265
00:18:13.859 --> 00:18:15.726
Did you take these?

266
00:18:15.795 --> 00:18:17.873
Back when I thought
I was a photographer.

267
00:18:17.897 --> 00:18:19.947
They're good. No. They're not.

268
00:18:20.015 --> 00:18:22.160
I stopped when I
realized I was terrible at it.

269
00:18:22.184 --> 00:18:23.729
Framing's off. bad lighting.

270
00:18:23.753 --> 00:18:26.148
Believe me. Not good.

271
00:18:26.172 --> 00:18:30.774
That was when I thought I was
into painting. Uh. terrible. too.

272
00:18:30.843 --> 00:18:33.344
That's when I tried poetry.

273
00:18:33.412 --> 00:18:36.908
"Terrible" doesn't even
come close to describing that.

274
00:18:36.932 --> 00:18:38.965
What are you good at?

275
00:18:40.453 --> 00:18:43.813
I'm gonna show you if
you promise not to laugh.

276
00:18:46.326 --> 00:18:47.903
I was nationally
ranked as a kid.

277
00:18:47.927 --> 00:18:49.371
And my dad really
wanted me to go on.

278
00:18:49.395 --> 00:18:51.039
but I don't know.
I didn't like it.

279
00:18:51.063 --> 00:18:53.614
Promise you won't laugh?

280
00:18:53.683 --> 00:18:57.451
I promise. What
the hell is that?

281
00:18:57.520 --> 00:18:58.969
It's a compound bow.

282
00:18:59.038 --> 00:19:01.522
And I'm pretty sure it
requires an arrow to be harmful.

283
00:19:03.259 --> 00:19:08.179
So that's what you're
good at. Archery.

284
00:19:08.247 --> 00:19:09.575
You said you wouldn't laugh.

285
00:19:09.599 --> 00:19:14.134
(CHUCKLES) Trust
me. I'm not laughing.

286
00:19:28.767 --> 00:19:30.478
So. I guess I should explain.

287
00:19:30.502 --> 00:19:34.438
We're not some sort of
separatist. gun nut family.

288
00:19:34.490 --> 00:19:37.007
My dad sells firearms
to the law enforcement.

289
00:19:38.260 --> 00:19:39.793
Oh. that's good.

290
00:19:42.465 --> 00:19:44.443
So you planning on
joining the family business?

291
00:19:44.467 --> 00:19:47.835
I don't know. You tell me.
Would I look hot with a gun?

292
00:19:50.406 --> 00:19:51.839
Hotter without.

293
00:19:54.176 --> 00:19:55.225
(DOOR OPENS)

294
00:19:55.294 --> 00:19:56.493
(GASPS)

295
00:20:00.749 --> 00:20:04.251
KATE: Hey Chris. get your ass out of
the '50s and come help with the groceries.

296
00:20:05.387 --> 00:20:06.921
CHRIS: Be right there.

297
00:20:12.144 --> 00:20:13.493
You two mind helping?

298
00:20:14.631 --> 00:20:16.591
Sure. No problem.

299
00:20:17.566 --> 00:20:18.732
Great.

300
00:20:21.671 --> 00:20:22.869
(SIGHS)

301
00:20:31.898 --> 00:20:33.538
Thank you. (PHONE CHIMES)

302
00:20:40.356 --> 00:20:41.466
Do you still wanna study?

303
00:20:41.490 --> 00:20:43.650
She'll concentrate
better on her own.

304
00:20:45.445 --> 00:20:47.077
Um...

305
00:20:47.146 --> 00:20:48.623
Guess I'll see you later then?

306
00:20:48.647 --> 00:20:50.097
CHRIS: At school.

307
00:20:52.285 --> 00:20:53.550
(INAUDIBLE)

308
00:20:53.619 --> 00:20:56.686
You. on your bike. You. inside.

309
00:20:56.755 --> 00:20:59.089
Oh. come on. Chris. really?

310
00:20:59.158 --> 00:21:03.794
They were making out in the
garage. not shooting amateur porn.

311
00:21:03.862 --> 00:21:07.398
You. with the adorable
brown eyes. drop your bike.

312
00:21:07.467 --> 00:21:09.827
You're staying for dinner.

313
00:21:19.328 --> 00:21:20.911
You eat meat?

314
00:21:28.237 --> 00:21:30.137
You don't mind?

315
00:21:30.206 --> 00:21:34.141
Actually. no. Gives us a
chance to get to know each other.

316
00:21:41.801 --> 00:21:43.668
(HEART BEATING LOUDLY)

317
00:21:43.736 --> 00:21:45.369
(DISHES CLANKING)

318
00:21:48.340 --> 00:21:51.675
Would you like something else
to drink besides water. Scott?

319
00:21:51.744 --> 00:21:54.044
Oh... No. I'm good. Thanks.

320
00:21:54.113 --> 00:21:56.433
We can get you some beer?

321
00:21:58.217 --> 00:22:00.251
No. thanks. Shot of tequila?

322
00:22:00.319 --> 00:22:01.936
Dad. really?

323
00:22:02.722 --> 00:22:04.054
You don't drink. Scott?

324
00:22:04.123 --> 00:22:05.423
I'm not old enough to.

325
00:22:05.491 --> 00:22:07.424
That doesn't seem to
stop many teenagers.

326
00:22:07.493 --> 00:22:09.126
No. but it should.

327
00:22:09.195 --> 00:22:11.256
Good answer. A total lie.

328
00:22:11.280 --> 00:22:13.463
but well played. Scott.

329
00:22:13.533 --> 00:22:15.733
You may yet survive the night.

330
00:22:16.969 --> 00:22:19.203
You ever smoke pot?

331
00:22:19.272 --> 00:22:23.607
Changing the channel to
something a little less conservative.

332
00:22:23.676 --> 00:22:27.411
So. Scott. Allison tells us
you're on the lacrosse team.

333
00:22:27.480 --> 00:22:30.325
I'm sorry. I don't know anything
about that. How do you play?

334
00:22:30.349 --> 00:22:32.849
Um. well. you know
hockey? Mmm-hmm.

335
00:22:32.918 --> 00:22:36.453
It's a lot like that. only
played on grass instead of ice.

336
00:22:38.791 --> 00:22:42.126
Hockey on grass is
called field hockey.

337
00:22:43.663 --> 00:22:46.129
Oh. yeah.

338
00:22:46.198 --> 00:22:51.201
So it's like field hockey.
except the sticks have nets.

339
00:22:51.270 --> 00:22:52.570
Exactly. (PHONE CHIMES)

340
00:22:52.638 --> 00:22:54.878
KATE: And can you
slap check like hockey?

341
00:22:55.224 --> 00:22:56.390
Um...

342
00:22:56.459 --> 00:22:59.443
Yeah. But it's only the
gloves and the sticks.

343
00:22:59.512 --> 00:23:02.078
Sounds violent. I like it.

344
00:23:02.147 --> 00:23:03.647
Scott's amazing. too.

345
00:23:03.716 --> 00:23:06.445
Dad came with me to the
first game. Wasn't he good?

346
00:23:06.469 --> 00:23:07.734
He was fine.

347
00:23:07.803 --> 00:23:10.621
He scored the last
shot. the winning shot.

348
00:23:10.690 --> 00:23:13.491
True. But he didn't score at
all until the last few minutes.

349
00:23:15.528 --> 00:23:19.196
His last shot ripped a hole through
the goalie's net. It was incredible!

350
00:23:19.265 --> 00:23:21.960
Well. I think the goalie was probably
playing with a defective stick. so...

351
00:23:21.984 --> 00:23:22.984
(BANGS)

352
00:23:23.052 --> 00:23:24.052
(CLANKING)

353
00:23:24.120 --> 00:23:25.986
(HEART BEATING LOUDLY)

354
00:23:34.263 --> 00:23:39.400
You know. on second thought. I
think I'll take that shot of tequila.

355
00:23:42.638 --> 00:23:43.987
(LAUGHING)

356
00:23:46.842 --> 00:23:49.043
You were kidding. right? Yeah.

357
00:23:50.546 --> 00:23:52.946
What am I supposed
to do with him?

358
00:23:53.015 --> 00:23:55.098
Take him somewhere. Anywhere!

359
00:23:55.167 --> 00:23:57.985
(SIGHS) And by the
way. he's starting to smell.

360
00:23:58.053 --> 00:24:00.070
<i>Like what?</i> Like death.

361
00:24:02.925 --> 00:24:04.885
Okay. Take him
to the animal clinic.

362
00:24:05.277 --> 00:24:06.543
What about your boss?

363
00:24:06.612 --> 00:24:07.811
He's gone by now.

364
00:24:07.880 --> 00:24:09.908
There's a spare key in the
box behind the dumpster.

365
00:24:09.932 --> 00:24:11.832
(SIGHS)

366
00:24:11.900 --> 00:24:14.546
You're not gonna believe
where he's telling me to take you.

367
00:24:14.570 --> 00:24:15.602
Did you find it?

368
00:24:15.671 --> 00:24:17.582
How am I supposed
to find one bullet?

369
00:24:17.606 --> 00:24:19.339
They have a million!

370
00:24:19.408 --> 00:24:22.387
This house is like the
freaking Walmart of guns!

371
00:24:22.411 --> 00:24:25.478
If you don't find it.
then I'm dead. all right?

372
00:24:25.548 --> 00:24:27.658
I'm starting to think that
wouldn't be such a bad thing.

373
00:24:27.682 --> 00:24:31.869
Then think about this. The Alpha
called you out against your will.

374
00:24:31.937 --> 00:24:33.436
<i>He's gonna do it again.</i>

375
00:24:33.506 --> 00:24:37.558
<i>Next time. you either kill
with him or you get killed.</i>

376
00:24:37.626 --> 00:24:41.295
So if want to stay alive. then
you need me. Find the bullet.

377
00:24:44.300 --> 00:24:45.899
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

378
00:24:53.542 --> 00:24:55.376
(ALARM BLARES)

379
00:24:55.444 --> 00:24:56.521
(KATE CLEARS THROAT)

380
00:24:56.545 --> 00:24:57.844
(ALARM STOPS)

381
00:24:57.913 --> 00:24:59.897
You look like a
little lost puppy.

382
00:24:59.965 --> 00:25:00.998
Um...

383
00:25:01.066 --> 00:25:03.216
I'm just looking
for the bathroom.

384
00:25:03.285 --> 00:25:06.887
Bathroom? Does that
look like a bathroom?

385
00:25:11.160 --> 00:25:12.559
No.

386
00:25:12.628 --> 00:25:15.095
No. Use the guest bedroom.

387
00:25:16.615 --> 00:25:18.465
Okay. Thanks.

388
00:25:31.814 --> 00:25:33.246
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

389
00:27:21.039 --> 00:27:22.138
(PHONE BEEPS)

390
00:27:22.207 --> 00:27:23.707
(DOGS BARKING)

391
00:27:26.428 --> 00:27:29.229
Does Nordic blue monkshood
mean anything to you?

392
00:27:29.298 --> 00:27:32.816
It's a rare form of wolfsbane.
He has to bring me the bullet.

393
00:27:32.885 --> 00:27:34.634
Why?

394
00:27:34.703 --> 00:27:36.486
Because I'm
gonna die without it.

395
00:27:39.257 --> 00:27:42.792
Hey. I should get going.
Um. thanks for dinner.

396
00:27:42.862 --> 00:27:45.073
Oh. no. You have
to stay for dessert.

397
00:27:45.097 --> 00:27:48.537
I want to know more
about you. Sit down.

398
00:27:49.084 --> 00:27:50.617
Okay.

399
00:27:50.703 --> 00:27:53.820
Allison was just telling us
that you work for a veterinarian.

400
00:27:53.889 --> 00:27:56.267
I told them how you put
the cast on the dog I hit.

401
00:27:56.291 --> 00:27:58.909
(PHONE CHIMES)

402
00:27:58.977 --> 00:28:02.495
What does your boss think of
the animal attacks? Any theories?

403
00:28:03.749 --> 00:28:05.615
Everyone's just saying
it's a mountain lion.

404
00:28:05.684 --> 00:28:07.250
(KATE LAUGHS)

405
00:28:07.319 --> 00:28:10.020
Have to be a pretty
large mountain lion.

406
00:28:10.089 --> 00:28:12.406
What do you think.
Scott? I don't know.

407
00:28:12.474 --> 00:28:15.341
We usually get cats and dogs
at the vet. Nothing that vicious.

408
00:28:15.410 --> 00:28:17.477
Never had to deal
with a rabid dog?

409
00:28:19.748 --> 00:28:23.200
Oh. I grew up
with a lot of dogs.

410
00:28:23.269 --> 00:28:25.702
I saw one get rabies from a bat.

411
00:28:25.771 --> 00:28:28.372
It was transferred
through the bite.

412
00:28:28.441 --> 00:28:31.619
People think that a rabid
dog suddenly goes mad.

413
00:28:31.643 --> 00:28:33.494
It's a lot more gradual.

414
00:28:33.562 --> 00:28:38.432
First stage is subtle changes in
behavior. They're restless. morose.

415
00:28:38.500 --> 00:28:42.469
It's the second stage that
people know. The furious phase.

416
00:28:42.538 --> 00:28:47.441
That's when they attack. And
we're talking any moving object.

417
00:28:47.509 --> 00:28:49.053
Did you know that a
caged. rabid dog will

418
00:28:49.077 --> 00:28:52.207
break its own teeth trying
to chew through the bars?

419
00:28:52.231 --> 00:28:54.509
It'll even rear back
and snap its own spine.

420
00:28:54.533 --> 00:28:58.335
Can you imagine the amount
of force it would take to do that?

421
00:28:59.739 --> 00:29:02.689
It's a complete
character reversal.

422
00:29:02.757 --> 00:29:07.477
This harmless animal turned
into a perfectly vicious killer.

423
00:29:08.680 --> 00:29:11.120
And it all started
with that one bite.

424
00:29:12.484 --> 00:29:13.645
But it died. didn't it?

425
00:29:13.669 --> 00:29:15.602
Yes. because your
grandfather shot it.

426
00:29:15.671 --> 00:29:17.065
Because he wanted
to put it out of its misery.

427
00:29:17.089 --> 00:29:19.255
CHRIS: Because it
was too dangerous.

428
00:29:19.324 --> 00:29:22.258
Something that out of
control is better off dead.

429
00:29:28.500 --> 00:29:29.633
Okay.

430
00:29:29.702 --> 00:29:31.301
(LIGHTS BUZZING)

431
00:29:34.406 --> 00:29:35.471
(DEREK BREATHING HEAVILY)

432
00:29:35.540 --> 00:29:37.507
You know. that
really doesn't look like

433
00:29:37.560 --> 00:29:41.127
anything some echinacea and a
good night's sleep couldn't take care of.

434
00:29:41.196 --> 00:29:43.908
When the infection
reaches my heart. it'll kill me.

435
00:29:43.932 --> 00:29:45.332
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

436
00:29:45.400 --> 00:29:47.967
Positivity just isn't in
your vocabulary. is it?

437
00:29:48.037 --> 00:29:52.572
If he doesn't get here with
the bullet in time. last resort...

438
00:29:52.641 --> 00:29:53.723
Which is?

439
00:29:55.460 --> 00:29:57.540
You're going to cut off my arm.

440
00:30:02.434 --> 00:30:04.334
I'm so incredibly sorry.

441
00:30:04.402 --> 00:30:05.936
For what?

442
00:30:06.004 --> 00:30:08.438
For that being the worst. most
horribly awkward dinner ever

443
00:30:08.506 --> 00:30:10.907
in the history of horribly
awkward dinners.

444
00:30:10.976 --> 00:30:13.676
No. it wasn't the worst.

445
00:30:14.646 --> 00:30:16.346
There was this one dinner

446
00:30:16.414 --> 00:30:19.216
where my parents told me
they were getting a divorce.

447
00:30:19.284 --> 00:30:21.524
This comes in a close second.

448
00:30:25.724 --> 00:30:27.741
Your dad's watching. Good.

449
00:30:35.984 --> 00:30:37.517
Wait a second. guys.

450
00:30:37.585 --> 00:30:39.552
What is it?

451
00:30:39.621 --> 00:30:43.073
Uh. I have to ask
Scott something. Me?

452
00:30:43.142 --> 00:30:44.774
Yeah. you.

453
00:30:44.843 --> 00:30:45.843
(DOOR CLOSES)

454
00:30:47.429 --> 00:30:48.545
Okay.

455
00:30:49.348 --> 00:30:51.481
Uh... (CHUCKLES)

456
00:30:51.550 --> 00:30:53.430
What did you take from my bag?

457
00:30:54.186 --> 00:30:56.836
What? My bag.

458
00:30:56.905 --> 00:30:58.705
What did you take from it?

459
00:31:00.492 --> 00:31:02.303
You need me to
repeat the question?

460
00:31:02.327 --> 00:31:03.771
Maybe enunciate more clearly?

461
00:31:03.795 --> 00:31:06.195
What are you talking about?

462
00:31:07.233 --> 00:31:10.683
My bag was open in the guest
room. and when I left. it was shut.

463
00:31:10.752 --> 00:31:15.672
And Scott comes in to use the
bathroom. He leaves. my bag's open.

464
00:31:15.741 --> 00:31:16.773
He didn't take anything.

465
00:31:16.842 --> 00:31:19.725
Something was taken from my bag.

466
00:31:19.794 --> 00:31:22.629
Now look. I hate to be
the accuser here. Scott.

467
00:31:22.698 --> 00:31:27.033
because I really do love
those adorable brown eyes.

468
00:31:27.102 --> 00:31:30.270
But I don't know if you're
a klepto. if you're curious.

469
00:31:30.339 --> 00:31:33.239
(LAUGHING) or if you're just
stupid. but answer the question.

470
00:31:33.942 --> 00:31:35.192
What did you take?

471
00:31:35.261 --> 00:31:37.310
Nothing. I swear.

472
00:31:39.448 --> 00:31:40.742
You don't mind
proving it. do you?

473
00:31:40.766 --> 00:31:41.999
Are you serious?

474
00:31:42.067 --> 00:31:43.361
How about you show
us what's in your pocket?

475
00:31:43.385 --> 00:31:44.618
Dad?

476
00:31:44.686 --> 00:31:47.471
Come on. Scott. Prove me wrong.

477
00:31:47.539 --> 00:31:49.973
I'll prove you wrong.

478
00:31:50.041 --> 00:31:53.410
Uh. it wasn't Scott going
through your bags. It was me.

479
00:31:53.478 --> 00:31:55.245
You? Mmm-hmm. Me.

480
00:31:55.314 --> 00:31:57.213
(UPBEAT POP-ROCK MUSIC)

481
00:31:59.551 --> 00:32:02.936
<i>♪ This way is ours
You can do it. do it</i>

482
00:32:03.005 --> 00:32:06.305
<i>♪ Won't be too hard Do it. do it</i>

483
00:32:08.477 --> 00:32:11.828
<i>♪ You can find a way</i>

484
00:32:11.896 --> 00:32:15.315
<i>♪ You can find a way</i>

485
00:32:15.384 --> 00:32:17.317
<i>♪ You can find a way</i>

486
00:32:17.386 --> 00:32:20.354
<i>♪ You can find a way ♪</i>

487
00:32:39.207 --> 00:32:43.076
Oh. my God! What
if you bleed to death?

488
00:32:43.144 --> 00:32:45.545
It'll heal if it works.

489
00:32:45.614 --> 00:32:46.913
Ugh!

490
00:32:46.981 --> 00:32:49.749
Look. I don't know
if I can do this.

491
00:32:49.818 --> 00:32:50.983
Why not?

492
00:32:51.052 --> 00:32:53.303
Well. because of the
cutting through the flesh.

493
00:32:53.372 --> 00:32:55.588
the sawing of the bone.
and especially the blood!

494
00:32:56.642 --> 00:32:58.742
You faint at the sight of blood?

495
00:32:58.810 --> 00:33:01.544
No. But I might at the
sight of a chopped-off arm!

496
00:33:01.613 --> 00:33:03.246
(SIGHS)

497
00:33:03.314 --> 00:33:05.515
All right. fine. How about this?

498
00:33:05.583 --> 00:33:08.346
Either you cut off my arm.
or I'm gonna cut off your head.

499
00:33:08.370 --> 00:33:10.821
Okay. you know. I'm so not
buying your threats anymore.

500
00:33:10.889 --> 00:33:14.641
Oh. my God! Okay. All right. bought.
sold. totally. I'll do it. I'll do it.

501
00:33:15.560 --> 00:33:17.294
What are you doing?

502
00:33:17.362 --> 00:33:18.578
(VOMITS)

503
00:33:18.646 --> 00:33:21.681
Holy God! What the hell is that?

504
00:33:21.750 --> 00:33:23.995
It's my body. it is
trying to heal itself.

505
00:33:24.019 --> 00:33:25.880
Well. it's not doing
a very good job of it.

506
00:33:25.904 --> 00:33:27.904
Now. you gotta do it now.

507
00:33:29.608 --> 00:33:31.752
Look. honestly. I don't
think I can. Just do it!

508
00:33:31.776 --> 00:33:37.163
Oh. my God. Okay. Oh.
my God. All right. here we go!

509
00:33:37.231 --> 00:33:39.749
SCOTT: Stiles? Scott?

510
00:33:39.817 --> 00:33:41.635
(PANTING)

511
00:33:41.703 --> 00:33:43.414
What the hell are you doing?

512
00:33:43.438 --> 00:33:44.454
(CHUCKLES)

513
00:33:44.523 --> 00:33:45.988
(THUDS)

514
00:33:46.058 --> 00:33:48.169
Oh. you just prevented
a lifetime of nightmares.

515
00:33:48.193 --> 00:33:49.292
Did you get it?

516
00:33:55.267 --> 00:33:56.860
What are you gonna do with it?

517
00:33:56.884 --> 00:33:58.124
I'm gonna...

518
00:34:00.622 --> 00:34:02.739
(CLANKING) No.
don't. No. no. no!

519
00:34:04.209 --> 00:34:05.575
(GRUMBLING)

520
00:34:08.096 --> 00:34:11.230
Derek? Derek. come on. Wake up!

521
00:34:11.300 --> 00:34:14.262
Scott. what the hell are
we gonna do? I don't know!

522
00:34:14.286 --> 00:34:15.435
I can't reach it.

523
00:34:15.504 --> 00:34:16.820
He's not waking up!

524
00:34:16.888 --> 00:34:18.070
(SIGHS)

525
00:34:19.675 --> 00:34:21.936
I think he's dying.
I think he's dead.

526
00:34:21.960 --> 00:34:23.176
Just hold on!

527
00:34:23.245 --> 00:34:24.977
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

528
00:34:26.748 --> 00:34:28.064
Come on.

529
00:34:42.848 --> 00:34:43.880
Oh!

530
00:34:43.949 --> 00:34:45.882
I got it! I got it!

531
00:34:45.951 --> 00:34:50.069
Please don't kill me
for this! Ugh! Ow! God!

532
00:34:50.672 --> 00:34:52.205
Give me that.

533
00:34:53.007 --> 00:34:54.691
Up. God.

534
00:34:59.197 --> 00:35:00.246
(GRUNTING)

535
00:35:02.267 --> 00:35:03.583
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

536
00:35:05.820 --> 00:35:07.436
(LIGHTER CLICKS)

537
00:35:18.517 --> 00:35:19.566
Ugh!

538
00:35:20.535 --> 00:35:21.685
(SCREAMS)

539
00:35:23.038 --> 00:35:24.504
(GROANING)

540
00:35:29.561 --> 00:35:30.927
(SCREAMING)

541
00:35:36.184 --> 00:35:40.837
That was awesome! Yes!

542
00:35:43.341 --> 00:35:45.008
Are you okay?

543
00:35:45.077 --> 00:35:47.177
Except for the agonizing pain?

544
00:35:47.245 --> 00:35:50.605
I'm guessing the ability to use
sarcasm is a good sign of health.

545
00:35:52.784 --> 00:35:55.819
Okay. we saved your life. which
means you're gonna leave us alone.

546
00:35:55.888 --> 00:35:57.503
You got that?

547
00:35:57.572 --> 00:35:59.483
And if you don't. I'm gonna
go back to Allison's dad.

548
00:35:59.507 --> 00:36:00.785
and I'm gonna
tell him everything.

549
00:36:00.809 --> 00:36:03.460
You gonna trust them?
You think they can help you?

550
00:36:03.528 --> 00:36:06.545
Why not? They're a lot
freaking nicer than you are!

551
00:36:08.433 --> 00:36:10.513
Yeah. I can show you
exactly how nice they are.

552
00:36:12.153 --> 00:36:14.403
What do you mean?

553
00:36:14.472 --> 00:36:16.005
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

554
00:36:24.582 --> 00:36:26.482
What are we doing here?

555
00:36:55.330 --> 00:36:56.796
Who is he?

556
00:36:57.966 --> 00:37:01.034
My uncle. Peter Hale.

557
00:37:04.973 --> 00:37:09.376
Is he like you? A werewolf?

558
00:37:11.113 --> 00:37:15.382
He was. Now he's
barely even human.

559
00:37:16.968 --> 00:37:19.680
Six years ago. my sister
and I were at school.

560
00:37:19.704 --> 00:37:22.064
Our house caught fire.

561
00:37:23.575 --> 00:37:25.775
Eleven people
were trapped inside.

562
00:37:28.613 --> 00:37:30.279
He was the only survivor.

563
00:37:32.617 --> 00:37:36.253
So what makes you so
sure that they set the fire?

564
00:37:37.722 --> 00:37:39.682
'Cause they're the only
ones that knew about us.

565
00:37:40.625 --> 00:37:42.876
Then they had a reason.

566
00:37:44.729 --> 00:37:46.896
Like what?

567
00:37:46.965 --> 00:37:49.085
You tell me what justifies this.

568
00:37:51.736 --> 00:37:55.672
They say they'll only kill an
adult and only with absolute proof.

569
00:37:55.741 --> 00:37:59.292
But there were people in my family
that were perfectly ordinary in that fire.

570
00:37:59.360 --> 00:38:03.696
This is what they do.
And it's what Allison will do.

571
00:38:03.765 --> 00:38:06.549
What are you doing?
How did you get in here?

572
00:38:06.617 --> 00:38:07.850
We were just leaving.

573
00:38:25.070 --> 00:38:27.803
Hey. um...

574
00:38:27.872 --> 00:38:32.208
I just thought maybe I could catch
you before I went to sleep. but...

575
00:38:32.277 --> 00:38:34.810
I wanted to say
sorry again for tonight.

576
00:38:36.281 --> 00:38:38.914
So call me.

577
00:39:13.785 --> 00:39:18.287
The one that attacked me
was big. It had width and power.

578
00:39:18.356 --> 00:39:21.257
But the one I shot
was lean and fast.

579
00:39:21.326 --> 00:39:23.406
Well. that would be Derek Hale.

580
00:39:23.711 --> 00:39:24.894
Are we sure?

581
00:39:25.813 --> 00:39:26.896
Mostly.

582
00:39:26.964 --> 00:39:28.765
How do we know
it's just two of them?

583
00:39:28.834 --> 00:39:31.417
We don't yet.

584
00:39:31.486 --> 00:39:35.721
But if Derek's still alive.
he will lead us to the Alpha.

585
00:39:35.790 --> 00:39:38.808
Take the pack leader.
Then take the pack.

586
00:39:38.877 --> 00:39:40.955
And we do it
according to the code.

587
00:39:40.979 --> 00:39:42.245
You and the code.

588
00:39:42.313 --> 00:39:43.873
It's there for a reason. Kate.

589
00:39:44.966 --> 00:39:46.299
Of course.

590
00:39:47.302 --> 00:39:48.651
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

591
00:39:51.540 --> 00:39:53.640
I always play by the rules.

591
00:39:54.305 --> 00:40:54.544
